// src/components/FaqSection.astro
---

<section class="section faq-section">
  <div class="container">
    
    <div class="badge-wrapper" data-aos="fade-up">
      <span class="badge-center">Got Questions?</span>
    </div>
    
    <h2 class="section-heading centered" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
      Everything You Need to Know
    </h2>
    
    <p class="section-subtitle centered" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="200">
      Quick answers to common questions about AI-powered lending automation
    </p>

    <!-- FAQ Categories Tabs -->
    <div class="faq-tabs" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="300">
      <button class="faq-tab active" data-category="all">All Questions</button>
      <button class="faq-tab" data-category="implementation">Implementation</button>
      <button class="faq-tab" data-category="platform">Platform</button>
      <button class="faq-tab" data-category="security">Security</button>
      <button class="faq-tab" data-category="pricing">Pricing</button>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Accordion -->
    <div class="faq-accordion" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="400">
      
      <!-- Implementation FAQs -->
      <div class="faq-item" data-category="implementation">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
              <polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span>How quickly can we implement Mentyx?</span>
          <span class="faq-arrow">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p><strong>Most lenders are live in 2-4 weeks.</strong> Here's the typical timeline:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Week 1:</strong> Discovery & configuration - map your workflows, loan types, and underwriting criteria</li>
            <li><strong>Week 2:</strong> Data migration & integration - connect your existing systems and import historical data</li>
            <li><strong>Week 3:</strong> Team training & testing - hands-on training for your team with real loan scenarios</li>
            <li><strong>Week 4:</strong> Go-live & support - process your first live loans with dedicated support</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="faq-note">Need to move faster? We've deployed in as little as 1 week for urgent situations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" data-category="implementation">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path d="M21 16V8a2 2 0 0 0-1-1.73l-7-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 0l-7 4A2 2 0 0 0 3 8v8a2 2 0 0 0 1 1.73l7 4a2 2 0 0 0 2 0l7-4A2 2 0 0 0 21 16z"/>
              <polyline points="3.27 6.96 12 12.01 20.73 6.96"/>
              <line x1="12" y1="22.08" x2="12" y2="12"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span>Do we need to migrate all our historical loan data?</span>
          <span class="faq-arrow">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p><strong>It's optional but recommended.</strong> Migrating historical data allows our AI to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Train on your specific loan portfolio for more accurate risk scoring</li>
            <li>Provide better benchmarking and portfolio analytics</li>
            <li>Enable comprehensive reporting across your entire lending history</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We handle the entire migration process - you just need to provide data exports from your current system. Most lenders migrate 6-24 months of historical loans.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" data-category="implementation">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/>
              <circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/>
              <path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/>
              <path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span>How much training does our team need?</span>
          <span class="faq-arrow">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p><strong>Minimal training required - most teams are productive within hours.</strong></p>
          <p>We provide role-specific training:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Loan Officers (2 hours):</strong> Borrower portal, application intake, document upload</li>
            <li><strong>Underwriters (4 hours):</strong> AI-assisted underwriting, risk scoring, decision workflows</li>
            <li><strong>Managers (3 hours):</strong> Reporting, analytics, policy configuration</li>
          </ul>
          <p>All training includes live Q&A, recorded sessions for future reference, and ongoing support via Slack/email.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Platform FAQs -->
      <div class="faq-item" data-category="platform">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2" ry="2"/>
              <line x1="8" y1="21" x2="16" y2="21"/>
              <line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12" y2="21"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span>Does Mentyx integrate with our existing systems?</span>
          <span class="faq-arrow">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p><strong>Yes - we integrate with 50+ popular lending, accounting, and CRM platforms.</strong></p>
          <p>Common integrations include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Loan Servicing:</strong> Mortgage Automator, LendingWise, Nortridge, FICS</li>
            <li><strong>Accounting:</strong> QuickBooks, Xero, NetSuite</li>
            <li><strong>CRM:</strong> Salesforce, HubSpot, Zoho</li>
            <li><strong>Banking:</strong> Plaid, Yodlee for bank verification</li>
            <li><strong>Credit:</strong> Experian, Equifax, TransUnion</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="faq-note">Don't see your system? We offer custom API integration for enterprise clients.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" data-category="platform">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/>
              <polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/>
              <line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/>
              <line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/>
              <polyline points="10 9 9 9 8 9"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span>What types of documents can the AI process?</span>
          <span class="faq-arrow">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p><strong>Our AI extracts data from 100+ document types with 95%+ accuracy.</strong></p>
          <p>Supported documents include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Financial:</strong> Bank statements, tax returns (1040, 1120, 1065), P&L statements, balance sheets</li>
            <li><strong>Credit:</strong> Credit reports (all 3 bureaus), FICO scores, payment histories</li>
            <li><strong>Real Estate:</strong> Appraisals, purchase agreements, title reports, property inspections</li>
            <li><strong>Identity:</strong> Driver's licenses, passports, articles of incorporation, operating agreements</li>
            <li><strong>Loan Docs:</strong> Existing loan statements, payoff letters, term sheets</li>
          </ul>
          <p>The AI handles PDFs, scanned images, photos, and even handwritten forms.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" data-category="platform">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path d="M9 19v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2zm0 0V9a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v10m-6 0a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v14a2 2 0 01-2 2h-2a2 2 0 01-2-2z"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span>How accurate is the AI risk scoring?</span>
          <span class="faq-arrow">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p><strong>95%+ accuracy on standard financial documents, improving to 98%+ after training on your data.</strong></p>
          <p>Our AI risk scoring:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Learns from your decisions:</strong> The more loans you process, the better it predicts your approval patterns</li>
            <li><strong>Flags outliers:</strong> Automatically identifies applications that fall outside your normal criteria</li>
            <li><strong>Explainable results:</strong> Every score includes the specific factors that influenced it</li>
            <li><strong>Human oversight:</strong> Final decisions always rest with your underwriting team</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="faq-note">Accuracy metrics are tracked in real-time on your analytics dashboard.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" data-category="platform">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/>
              <polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/>
              <line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span>What types of loans does Mentyx support?</span>
          <span class="faq-arrow">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p><strong>All asset-based lending products:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Real Estate:</strong> Fix & flip, bridge loans, hard money, DSCR, construction, ground-up, cash-out refi</li>
            <li><strong>Commercial:</strong> Equipment financing, invoice factoring, merchant cash advances, inventory financing</li>
            <li><strong>Specialty:</strong> Cannabis lending, crypto-backed loans, litigation finance, royalty financing</li>
            <li><strong>Multi-Family:</strong> Small balance apartment loans, workforce housing, value-add multifamily</li>
          </ul>
          <p>If you lend against an asset (not consumer income), Mentyx supports it. Custom loan types can be configured during implementation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Security FAQs -->
      <div class="faq-item" data-category="security">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span>How secure is our data on Mentyx?</span>
          <span class="faq-arrow">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p><strong>Bank-grade security with SOC 2 Type II compliance.</strong></p>
          <p>Security measures include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> AES-256 encryption at rest, TLS 1.3 in transit</li>
            <li><strong>Access Control:</strong> Multi-factor authentication (MFA), role-based permissions, IP whitelisting</li>
            <li><strong>Infrastructure:</strong> AWS GovCloud hosting, redundant backups, 99.9% uptime SLA</li>
            <li><strong>Monitoring:</strong> 24/7 security monitoring, automated threat detection, intrusion prevention</li>
            <li><strong>Compliance:</strong> SOC 2 Type II, GDPR compliant, annual penetration testing</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="faq-note">We maintain complete audit trails of all data access and system changes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" data-category="security">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path d="M9 5H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2M9 5a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2M9 5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2m-3 7h3m-3 4h3m-6-4h.01M9 16h.01"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span>Do you maintain audit trails for compliance?</span>
          <span class="faq-arrow">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p><strong>Yes - complete audit trails for every action and decision.</strong></p>
          <p>We track and log:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>All user actions (who did what, when)</li>
            <li>Document access and modifications</li>
            <li>Underwriting decisions and overrides</li>
            <li>Policy changes and approvals</li>
            <li>System configuration changes</li>
            <li>Data exports and report generation</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Audit logs are immutable, timestamped, and retained for 7 years. Perfect for regulatory exams and investor due diligence.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" data-category="security">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path d="M3 9l9-7 9 7v11a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2z"/>
              <polyline points="9 22 9 12 15 12 15 22"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span>Can we host Mentyx on our own servers?</span>
          <span class="faq-arrow">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p><strong>Yes - we offer on-premise and private cloud deployment for enterprise clients.</strong></p>
          <p>Deployment options:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>SaaS (Standard):</strong> Hosted by Mentyx on AWS, fastest implementation</li>
            <li><strong>Private Cloud:</strong> Dedicated AWS instance in your VPC, full data isolation</li>
            <li><strong>On-Premise:</strong> Installed on your infrastructure, complete control</li>
          </ul>
          <p>On-premise and private cloud require enterprise licenses. Contact us for custom deployment options.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Pricing FAQs -->
      <div class="faq-item" data-category="pricing">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <line x1="12" y1="1" x2="12" y2="23"/>
              <path d="M17 5H9.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 0 7h5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0 7H6"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span>How is Mentyx priced?</span>
          <span class="faq-arrow">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p><strong>Flexible pricing based on your loan volume and feature needs.</strong></p>
          <p>Pricing models:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Per-loan:</strong> Pay only for loans processed (best for &lt;50 loans/month)</li>
            <li><strong>Monthly subscription:</strong> Flat fee based on user count and volume (best for 50-200 loans/month)</li>
            <li><strong>Enterprise:</strong> Custom pricing for high-volume lenders (200+ loans/month)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>All plans include unlimited document processing, API access, and standard support. No hidden fees or long-term contracts.</p>
          <p class="faq-note">Schedule a demo for a personalized quote based on your needs.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" data-category="pricing">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
